{"type":"message","id":"625673e6","parentId":"be0ccdc8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:55:47.987Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2avo8trxib9b_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 035424\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. The big pending item is the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n3. Next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n\r\nThe most impactful action right now would be to start implementing the TIC classifier. This is the next experiment that tests the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what TIC would do:\r\n- Analyze the last 20 pulse logs\r\n- Classify content as invariant (stable across pulses) vs variant (changing)\r\n- Use invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n- Success criteria: >70% classification accuracy, >60% prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nTo implement this, I should:\r\n1. Create a script or module that reads pulse logs\r\n2. Extract features that distinguish invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Build a simple classifier\r\n4. Test on the logs\r\n\r\nSince I need to be specific and do file edits, I should:\r\n1. First, look at the existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create the TIC implementation\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist. The recent one mentioned is `pulse_2026-03-24 035215.md`.\r\n\r\nActually, let me focus on creating a concrete implementation file. I'll create a TIC classifier script that:\r\n- Reads the pulse logs\r\n- Identifies invariant patterns (things that repeat across pulses)\r\n- Classifies content\r\n- Attempts prediction\r\n\r\nLet me create this implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can distinguish invariant patterns from variant content across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the initial TIC classifier implementation that reads pulse logs, extracts invariant/variant patterns, and measures classification accuracy against success criteria (>70%).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    def __init__(self, logs_dir=\"logs\"):\r\n        self.logs_dir = Path(logs_dir)\r\n        self.invariant_patterns = []  # Patterns stable across pulses\r\n        self.variant_patterns = []    # Patterns that change between pulses\r\n        \r\n    def load_pulse_logs(self, n=20):\r\n        \"\"\"Load last n pulse log files.\"\"\"\r\n        logs = sorted(self.logs_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))[-n:]\r\n        return [log.read_text() for log in logs]\r\n    \r\n    def extract_features(self, text):\r\n        \"\"\"Extract structural features from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n        features = {\r\n            'sections': re.findall(r'^#{1,3}\\s+(.+)$', text, re.MULTILINE),\r\n            'actions': re.findall(r'### ACTION\\n(.+?)(?:\\n###|$)', text, re.DOTALL),\r\n            'mutations': re.findall(r'### MUTATION\\n```\\n(.+?)\\n```', text, re.DOTALL),\r\n            'goals': re.findall(r'- \\[ \\] (.+)|- \\[x\\] (.+)', text),\r\n            'word_count': len(text.split()),\r\n            'has_insight': '## Key Insights' in text,\r\n            'has_pending': '## Pending' in text,\r\n        }\r\n        return features\r\n    \r\n    def compute_invariants(self, features_list):\r\n        \"\"\"Find patterns that persist across all pulses.\"\"\"\r\n        if not features_list:\r\n            return [], []\r\n        \r\n        # Section headers that appear in all/nearly all pulses are invariant\r\n        section_counts = Counter()\r\n        for feats in features_list:\r\n            for section in feats['sections']:\r\n                section_counts[section] += 1\r\n        \r\n        invariant_sections = [s for s, c in section_counts.items() \r\n                              if c >= len(features_list) * 0.7]\r\n        \r\n        # Actions that repeat are variant (different each pulse)\r\n        all_actions = [a.strip() for feats in features_list for a in feats['actions']]\r\n        action_counts = Counter(all_actions)\r\n        variant_actions = [a for a, c in action_counts.items() if c == 1]\r\n        \r\n        return invariant_sections, variant_actions\r\n    \r\n    def classify_content(self, text, invariants):\r\n        \"\"\"Classify content as invariant (causal) or variant.\"\"\"\r\n        features = self.extract_features(text)\r\n        is_invariant = any(inv in text for inv in invariants)\r\n        return 'invariant' if is_invariant else 'variant'\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next_pulse(self, current_features, invariants):\r\n        \"\"\"Predict what next pulse will contain based on invariants.\"\"\"\r\n        predicted = {\r\n            'will_have_insight': True,  # Invariant pattern\r\n            'will_have_goals': True,     # Invariant pattern\r\n            'will_have_pending': True,   # Invariant pattern\r\n            'will_have_action': len(current_features['actions']) > 0,\r\n            'predictions_based_on': invariants[:5]  # Top 5 invariants\r\n        }\r\n        return predicted\r\n    \r\n    def run_experiment(self, n_logs=20):\r\n        \"\"\"Run full TIC experiment.\"\"\"\r\n        logs = self.load_pulse_logs(n_logs)\r\n        features_list = [self.extract_features(log) for log in logs]\r\n        \r\n        # Step 1: Compute invariants across all pulses\r\n        invariants, variants = self.compute_invariants(features_list)\r\n        \r\n        # Step 2\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:54:58\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774338947985}}
{"type":"message","id":"218e667e","parentId":"625673e6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:55:58.793Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also read the most recent pulse log that was just created (035424) to see the full picture of what happened in this pulse cycle.","thinkingSignature":"09682df8534755097cb9c60d3ed21dbf12b2c23b5e3fccf0c39cd44056075a9c"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 03:55 AM**\n\n**What happened:** TIC experiment planning + code scaffold written.\n\n**Key observations from this cycle:**\n- COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis is still active and central\n- The classifier (`TICClassifier`) was scaffolded to:\n  - Load last 20 pulse logs\n  - Extract structural features (sections, actions, mutations, goals)\n  - Compute **invariants** (patterns stable across ≥70% of pulses)\n  - Classify content as invariant vs variant\n  - Predict next pulse content from invariant patterns\n- Success criteria: >70% classification accuracy, >60% prediction accuracy\n\n**Status:** `pulse_2026-03-24 035424.md` — new file created with the TIC implementation sketch.\n\n**Next steps (from the pulse):** The implementation needs to be completed (the `run_experiment` method is truncated at \"Step 2\"), and the classifier needs to be run against actual logs to measure against success criteria."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1972,"output":252,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14178,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774338947987}}
